==How It Works==
Clicking on the jukebox will open up a list of music that can be listened on the home screen. However, playing one will cost 'Furniture Coins' & must be paid per loop. It may be set as the default by clicking the blue button at the top right corner of the music player window. Clicking the 'X' button will cancel it & '''will not''' refund the coins.

The default will remain even when swapped with another furniture, so the jukebox does not have to always be in use.

With the Jukebox Kai, some kanmusu will make it difficult to click on the item; therefore, it's recommended to use smaller kanmusu during track changes.

Only tracks with 母港BGM設定可能 option can be set as the default, thus excluding [[Merchandise/Audio#Vocal Collections|Vocal Collection]] tracks.

→ [[Furniture#Guide|Further details about the process &amp; funding]].
